# How to configure Amazon VPC to communicate into internet and more

- Log in to your Amazon VPC using your root account

Subjects to configure based on your needed scenarios

IP range - CIDR
VPC define a list of CIDR IPv4 & IPv6
Subnets
Internet Gateway
Route Tables
Bastion Host
NAT Instances
NAT Gateway
NACL
Security Groups
VPC Peering
VPC Endpoints
VPC Flow Logs
Site-to-Site VPN
AWS VPN CloudHub
Direct Connect
Direct Connect Gateway
AWS PrivateLink / VPC Enpoint Services
ClassicLink
Transit Gateway
Traffic Miroring
Egress-only Internet Gateway - similar a NAT Gateway, but for IPV6 

